<lines>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_1">sine vsura vni vendi posse praesenti</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_2">pecunia pretio infimo, &amp; alij ad credi¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_3">tum, pretio summo intra dictam latitu¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_4">dinem; quia etiam praesenti pecunia</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_5">pretio summo posset venire. //Ita *@Caiet.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_6">2.2. q. 77. ar. 1. ad 1.@ @Mol. disp. 347. prope</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_7">fin.@ @Ioannes de Medin. C. de restitutione</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_8">q. 31.@ @Soto 6. de iust. q. 2. art. 3.@ @Couarr. 2.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_9">var. cap. 3. ad fi.n. 4.@ &amp; @Doctores commu¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_10">niter@*; &amp; sequitur euidenter ex dicta la¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_11">titudine pretij iusti. //*@S. Faustinus de em¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_12">ptione q. 5.n.7. qui bene n. 7.@* probat diem,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_13">&amp; horam esse inspiciendum ad pretiū;</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_14">*&amp; @Soto lib. 6. q. 2. ar. 3.@*</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_15">¶//Pretium conuentionale tertio loco</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_16">ingreditur non existente in rep. neque</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_17">pretio legali, quia non est taxatum à</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_18">principe, neque naturali, quia non est</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_19">recepta in rep. emptio, &amp; venditio illius</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_20">rei, puta accipitris alicuius, falconis, exi¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_21">miae alicuius picturae, grandioris gem¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_22">mae, generosi equi, egregiae, &amp; splendi¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_23">dae vestis. //Quia ergo tunc emptor, &amp;</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_24">venditor de pretio legali, aut naturali,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_25">idest currente in republica conuenire</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_26">non possunt, quia non est, conueniunt</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_27">de pretio ad suum arbitrium considera¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_28">tis circumstantijs, quae pretium natura¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_29">le iuste constituunt, &amp; ideo hoc pretiū</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_30">conuentionale dicitur. //Quod sine du¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_31">bio magis habet de arbitrio, &amp; latitudi¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_32">ne, quam pretium legale, aut naturale.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_33">//Et eandem latitudinem pretij conuen¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_34">tionalis habent aliquae actiones ad con¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_35">tractum locationis, &amp; cōductionis per¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_36">tinentes; quia nec lege taxantur, nec</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_37">vsu reip. vt aliqua eximia repraesentatio</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_38">funibuli volatio, allegatio Doctoris, li¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_39">beralis artis alicuius eximium magiste¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_40">rium. //Ita hoc pretium conuentionale</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_41">aliqui Doctores explicarunt; &amp; alij, qui</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_42">nomen tacuerunt, rem asserunt: &amp; re¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_43">uera nisi hoc pretium conuentionale</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_44">addatur, diuisio pretij in legale, &amp; natu¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_45">rale in sufficiens est, &amp; diminuta.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_46">¶//Sed quaestionis est non leuis: Vtrum</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_47">huiusmodi res, quę nec habent pretium</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_48">legale, quia non sunt taxatae, neque na¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_49">turale, quia non consueuerunt emi, &amp;</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_50">vendi in rep. quocumque pretio indif¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_51">ferente pro arbitrio, &amp; libito contrahē¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_52">tium emi, vendique possint. //Quod est</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_53">quaerere, vtrum pretium conuentionale</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_54">ad libitum emptoris, &amp; venditoris con¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_55">uenientium in infinitum excrescere ad</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_56">quamcumque quantitatem, vel decre¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_57">scere possit, vel habeat etiam suam lati¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_58">tudinem, &amp; fines, quos vltra, citraque</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_59">nequit consistere iustum conuentionale</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_60">pretium.</line>
</lines>
